        <p>BROUGHT TO YOU BY...Helene Bernardo letter abhors proliferation of advertising (Jan 15 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anywhere the Eye Can See, It's Now Likely to See an Ad'' (front page, Jan. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anywhere the Eye Can See, It's Now Likely to See an Ad'' (front page, Jan. 15):</p>
        <p>I can just see it now -- Welcome to the pearly gates, courtesy of Tiffany!</p>
        <p>Enough is enough!</p>
        <p>Helene Benardo  Bronx, Jan. 15, 2007</p>
      </block>
